member.remarks:

Pyramid chart control is used to visualize the proportions of a total in hierarchies.

SfPyramidChart class allows to customize the chart elements such as legend, data label, and tooltip features. 

             # [MainPage.xaml](#tab/tabid-1)

             <chart:SfPyramidChart  ItemsSource="{Binding Data}" 
                                    XBindingPath="XValue" 
                                    YBindingPath="YValue">
                  <chart:SfPyramidChart.BindingContext>
                      <model:ChartViewModel/>
                  </chart:SfPyramidChart.BindingContext>
             </chart:SfPyramidChart>


             # [MainPage.xaml.cs](#tab/tabid-2)

             SfPyramidChart chart = new SfPyramidChart();
             ChartViewModel viewModel = new ChartViewModel();
             chart.ItemsSource = viewModel.Data;
             chart.XBindingPath = "XValue";
             chart.YBindingPath = "YValue";


             # [ViewModel.cs](#tab/tabid-3)

             public ObservableCollection<Model> Data { get; set; }

             public ViewModel()
             {
                Data = new ObservableCollection<Model>();
                Data.Add(new Model() { XValue = "Stage A", YValue = 18 });
                Data.Add(new Model() { XValue = "Stage B", YValue = 20 });
                Data.Add(new Model() { XValue = "Stage C", YValue = 29 });
                Data.Add(new Model() { XValue = "Stage D", YValue = 33 });
             }


             ***


Legend


The Legend contains list of data points in chart. The information provided in each legend item helps to identify the corresponding data point in pyramid chart. The chart  property value will be displayed in the associated legend item.


To render a legend, create an instance of , and assign it to the  property. 

             # [MainPage.xaml](#tab/tabid-4)

             <chart:SfPyramidChart ItemsSource = "{Binding Data}"
                                   XBindingPath="XValue" 
                                   YBindingPath="YValue">
               <chart:SfPyramidChart.Legend>
                    <chart:ChartLegend/>
               </chart:SfPyramidChart.Legend>
             </chart:SfPyramidChart>


             # [MainPage.xaml.cs](#tab/tabid-5)

             SfPyramidChart chart = new SfPyramidChart();
             chart.Legend = new ChartLegend();
             ChartViewModel viewModel = new ChartViewModel();
             chart.ItemsSource = viewModel.Data;
             chart.XBindingPath = "XValue";
             chart.YBindingPath = "YValue";


             ***


Tooltip


Tooltip displays information while tapping or mouse hover on the segment. To display the tooltip on the chart, you need to set the  property as true in . 


To customize the appearance of the tooltip elements like Background, TextColor and Font, create an instance of  class, modify the values, and assign it to the chart’s  property. 

             # [MainPage.xaml](#tab/tabid-6)

             <chart:SfPyramidChart ItemsSource = "{Binding Data}"
                                   XBindingPath="XValue" 
                                   YBindingPath="YValue"
                                   EnableTooltip="True">
             </chart:SfPyramidChart>


             # [MainPage.xaml.cs](#tab/tabid-7)

             SfPyramidChart chart = new SfPyramidChart();
             ChartViewModel viewModel = new ChartViewModel();
             chart.ItemsSource = viewModel.Data;
             chart.XBindingPath = "XValue";
             chart.YBindingPath = "YValue";
             chart.EnableTooltip=true;



             ***


Data Label


Data labels are used to display values related to a chart segment. To render the data labels, you need to enable the  property as true in  class. 


To customize the chart data labels alignment, placement and label styles, need to create an instance of  and set to the  property.

             # [MainPage.xaml](#tab/tabid-8)

             <chart:SfPyramidChart  ItemsSource="{Binding Data}" 
                                    XBindingPath="XValue" 
                                    YBindingPath="YValue"
                                    ShowDataLabels="True">
             </chart:SfPyramidChart>


